                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/297: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-17T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 17, 1934—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Please appropriately communicate the following to Reina Andrade. “I take
                    great pleasure in acknowledging the receipt of your courteous message informing
                    me of the inauguration of the Conference in Guatemala City between delegates
                    from the republics of Central America. I extend my hearty good wishes for the
                    success of the Conference, and warmly reciprocate your assurances of high
                    consideration. Cordell Hull, Secretary of State of the United States.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
